biolockj.node.wgs

Class SlimmNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • biolockj.node.OtuNodeImpl
      • biolockj.node.wgs.SlimmNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OtuNode

    public class SlimmNode
extends OtuNodeImpl
implements OtuNode
    This class represents one line of SlimmClassifier output. SLIMM generates a separate output file for each taxonomy level for each sample, so the full taxonomy path cannot be determined with current BioLockJ implementation. Each line represents number of reads = 4th column (NoOfReads)

    2 sample lines (header + 1st row) of a SLIMM phylum level report (named 7A_1_phylum_reported.tsv):
    No. Name Taxid NoOfReads RelativeAbundance Contributers Coverage
    1 Bacteroidetes 976 1137994 29.7589 17 24.7204

    • Constructor Detail

      • SlimmNode

        public SlimmNode(String fileName,
                 String line)
          throws Exception
        SLIMM splits OTU reports into separate tab-delimited files, so we do not have the full taxonomy path.
        • Sample ID and taxonomy level are extracted from fileName.
        • Taxonomy (column 2) and count (column 4) are extracted from the line.
        Parameters:
        fileName - File name contains Sample ID and report taxonomy level
        line - SLIMM taxonomy level report line
        Throws:
        Exception - if unable to extract valid taxonomy level from fileName
